{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775868478775,"sessionID":"ses_285ff12c3ffeUtlyBcmJBkV4Hs","part":{"id":"prt_d7a028535001bhTi43pCK2OPYN","messageID":"msg_d7a027b4b0012F7lnLSQu9ukov","sessionID":"ses_285ff12c3ffeUtlyBcmJBkV4Hs","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775868550914,"sessionID":"ses_285ff12c3ffeUtlyBcmJBkV4Hs","part":{"id":"prt_d7a039e2b00119CTaiH5R5t8qT","messageID":"msg_d7a027b4b0012F7lnLSQu9ukov","sessionID":"ses_285ff12c3ffeUtlyBcmJBkV4Hs","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-d0431ee25e964f3a81201906f89d476d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Specification — CLI pack Command\n\nAR: AR-020 — CLI pack 命令\nModule: cmd/cli\nLanguage: Python\nSize: M\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Pack Command Entry Point\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `pack` subcommand via Typer application to validate and prepare a workspace, merge CLI overrides into metadata, optionally generate a Dockerfile, and report paths.\n\n### Scenario: Options and Defaults\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack` without specifying any options\n- **WHEN** the command is invoked\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL use the following defaults:\n  - `workspace` = \".\" (`-f` / `--workspace`, type `str`)\n  - `agent_name` = `None` (`--agent-name`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `language` = `None` (`--language`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `entrypoint` = `None` (`--entrypoint`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `port` = `None` (`--port`, type `Optional[int]`)\n  - `build_mode` = `None` (`--build-mode`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `description` = `None` (`--description`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `output` = `None` (`--output`, type `Optional[str]`)\n  - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, type `bool`)\n\n### Scenario: Successful Pack\n\n- **GIVEN** a valid workspace path with required files for the specified language\n- **WHEN** `pack` completes without exception\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Display a Rich Progress spinner during execution\n  - Print success message including `agent_name`, resolved `workspace_path`, and `metadata_path`\n  - Report `metadata_path` as `{final_workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`\n\n### Scenario: Pack Failure Handling with Verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red\n  - Print the full traceback\n  - Exit with code `1`\n\n### Scenario: Pack Failure Handling without Verbose\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` raises an exception\n- **WHEN** `verbose` is `False`\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print `Error packaging agent: {e}` in red\n  - Exit with code `1` without printing traceback\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Workspace Validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate that the workspace path exists, is a directory, and contains language-specific required files.\n\n### Scenario: Missing Workspace Directory\n\n- **GIVEN** the `workspace_path` does not exist on the filesystem\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the directory does not exist\n\n### Scenario: Workspace is Not a Directory\n\n- **GIVEN** the `workspace_path` exists but is not a directory\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_workspace_structure` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the path is not a directory\n\n### Scenario: Python Workspace Without Python Files\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"` and the workspace is a valid directory\n- **WHEN** no `*.py` files exist in the workspace root\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError(\"No Python files found in workspace\")`\n\n### Scenario: Java Workspace Without pom.xml\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"` and the workspace is a valid directory\n- **WHEN** no `pom.xml` file exists in the workspace\n- **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` indicating `pom.xml` is required for Java projects\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Metadata Loading and Creation\n\nThe system SHALL load existing metadata from YAML or create new metadata with defaults when the file does not exist.\n\n### Scenario: Load Existing Metadata from Primary File\n\n- **GIVEN** `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata from `agent_metadata.yaml` and parse as `AgentMetadata`\n\n### Scenario: Load Existing Metadata from Fallback Files\n\n- **GIVEN** `agent_metadata.yaml` does not exist but `agent.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata from `agent.yaml`\n\n### Scenario: Load Existing Metadata from Secondary Fallback\n\n- **GIVEN** neither `agent_metadata.yaml` nor `agent.yaml` exists but `metadata.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL load metadata from `metadata.yaml`\n\n### Scenario: Create New Metadata When No File Exists\n\n- **GIVEN** none of `agent_metadata.yaml`, `agent.yaml`, or `metadata.yaml` exist\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._load_or_create_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Create a new `AgentMetadata` with default values\n  - Set `agent_name` from CLI option or infer from workspace directory name\n  - Set `language` from CLI option or default to \"python\"\n  - Set `port` from CLI option or default to `8080`\n  - Set `build_mode` from CLI option or default to \"local\"\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Option Overrides\n\nThe system SHALL merge CLI option overrides into loaded or created metadata.\n\n### Scenario: Override Agent Name\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata exists with `agent_name = \"original-name\"`\n- **WHEN** CLI option `--agent-name \"new-name\"` is provided\n- **THEN** `PackRuntime._apply_option_overrides` SHALL update `agent_name` to \"new-name\"\n\n### Scenario: Override Language\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata exists with `language = \"python\"`\n- **WHEN** CLI option `--language java` is provided\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update `language` to \"java\" and validate Java workspace compatibility\n\n### Scenario: Override Entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata exists with `entrypoint = \"python main.py\"`\n- **WHEN** CLI option `--entrypoint \"python app.py\"` is provided\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update `entrypoint` to \"python app.py\"\n\n### Scenario: Override Port\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata exists with `port = 8080`\n- **WHEN** CLI option `--port 9000` is provided\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update `port` to `9000` and validate the port range `1..65535`\n\n### Scenario: Override Build Mode\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata exists with `build_mode = \"local\"`\n- **WHEN** CLI option `--build-mode cloud` is provided\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update `build_mode` to \"cloud\"\n\n### Scenario: Override Description\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata exists with `description = None`\n- **WHEN** CLI option `--description \"My AI agent\"` is provided\n- **THEN** the system SHALL update `description` to \"My AI agent\"\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Language Compatibility Validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate workspace compatibility with the specified or inferred language.\n\n### Scenario: Validate Python Workspace Structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"python\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_python_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Check for presence of at least one `*.py` file\n  - Optionally check for `requirements.txt` or `pyproject.toml`\n  - Raise `ValueError` if Python files are missing\n\n### Scenario: Validate Java Workspace Structure\n\n- **GIVEN** `metadata.language == \"java\"`\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._validate_java_compatibility` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Check for presence of `pom.xml`\n  - Raise `ValueError` if `pom.xml` is missing\n\n### Scenario: Invalid Language Value\n\n- **GIVEN** CLI option `--language ruby` is provided\n- **WHEN** metadata is validated\n- **THEN** Pydantic SHALL raise validation error because `language` must be `python` or `java` (lowercase)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Entrypoint Inference\n\nThe system SHALL infer the entrypoint command based on language and workspace contents when not explicitly provided.\n\n### Scenario: Infer Python Entrypoint from main.py\n\n- **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `entrypoint` is not provided\n- **WHEN** `main.py` exists in the workspace\n- **THEN** `PackRuntime._infer_entrypoint` SHALL return `\"python main.py\"`\n\n### Scenario: Infer Python Entrypoint from app.py\n\n- **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `entrypoint` is not provided and `main.py` does not exist\n- **WHEN** `app.py` exists in the workspace\n- **THEN** the system SHALL infer `\"python app.py\"`\n\n### Scenario: Infer Python Entrypoint from First py File\n\n- **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and neither `main.py` nor `app.py` exist\n- **WHEN** other `*.py` files exist (e.g., `agent.py`)\n- **THEN** the system SHALL infer `\"python {first_py_file}\"`\n\n### Scenario: Infer Java Entrypoint\n\n- **GIVEN** `language = \"java\"` and `entrypoint` is not provided\n- **WHEN** `pom.xml` exists\n- **THEN** the system SHALL infer a Maven-based entrypoint (e.g., `\"java -jar target/*.jar\"` or appropriate command)\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Dependency Processing\n\nThe system SHALL process language-specific dependencies and prepare them for containerization.\n\n### Scenario: Process Python Dependencies from requirements.txt\n\n- **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `requirements.txt` exists\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_python_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Copy `requirements.txt` to the packaging context\n  - Record `requirements_file` in metadata as `\"requirements.txt\"`\n\n### Scenario: Process Python Dependencies from pyproject.toml\n\n- **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and `pyproject.toml` exists (no `requirements.txt`)\n- **WHEN** dependency processing runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL handle `pyproject.toml` based dependencies\n\n### Scenario: Process Java Dependencies from pom.xml\n\n- **GIVEN** `language = \"java\"` and `pom.xml` exists\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._process_java_dependencies` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL copy `pom.xml` and prepare Maven build context\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Dockerfile Generation\n\nThe system SHALL generate a language-appropriate Dockerfile when one does not exist in the workspace.\n\n### Scenario: Generate Python Dockerfile\n\n- **GIVEN** `language = \"python\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_python_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the generated Dockerfile SHALL:\n  - Use a Python base image (e.g., `python:3.10-slim`)\n  - Install dependencies from `requirements.txt` if present\n  - Copy source files\n  - Set the entrypoint from metadata\n  - Expose the port from metadata\n\n### Scenario: Generate Java Dockerfile\n\n- **GIVEN** `language = \"java\"` and no existing Dockerfile\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_java_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the generated Dockerfile SHALL:\n  - Use a Maven/Java base image (multi-stage build)\n  - Build from `pom.xml`\n  - Copy the built JAR\n  - Set the entrypoint from metadata\n  - Expose the port from metadata\n\n### Scenario: Skip Dockerfile Generation if Exists\n\n- **GIVEN** a `Dockerfile` already exists in the workspace\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._generate_dockerfile` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Not overwrite the existing Dockerfile\n  - Return `None` or the path to the existing Dockerfile\n  - Log that existing Dockerfile will be used\n\n### Scenario: Dockerfile Path Update in Metadata\n\n- **GIVEN** a Dockerfile is generated or exists\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._update_pack_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the metadata SHALL be updated with Dockerfile path reference\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Output Path Preparation\n\nThe system SHALL prepare the output path for packaging when specified.\n\n### Scenario: Use Specified Output Path\n\n- **GIVEN** CLI option `--output /path/to/output.tar.gz` is provided\n- **WHEN** `PackRuntime._prepare_output_path` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Validate the parent directory exists\n  - Return the absolute path for the output archive\n\n### Scenario: Default Output Path\n\n- **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n- **WHEN** output path is prepared\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use a default output location based on workspace (e.g., `{workspace}/{agent_name}-packaged.tar.gz`)\n\n### Scenario: Create Output Parent Directory\n\n- **GIVEN** output path parent directory does not exist\n- **WHEN** output path is prepared\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create the parent directory\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Metadata Schema Validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate metadata against the `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model.\n\n### Scenario: Valid Metadata Fields\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata YAML is loaded\n- **WHEN** `AgentMetadata` model validation runs\n- **THEN** all fields SHALL conform to their types and constraints:\n  - `agent_name` is required `str`\n  - `language` is `str` with validator allowing only `python` or `java` (lowercase)\n  - `port` is `int` in range `1..65535`\n  - `build_mode` is `str` with validator allowing only `local` or `cloud` (lowercase)\n\n### Scenario: Invalid Language Rejected\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `language = \"ruby\"`\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n- **THEN** the validator SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating language must be `python` or `java`\n\n### Scenario: Invalid Port Range Rejected\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `port = 70000`\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n- **THEN** the validator SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating port must be in range `1..65535`\n\n### Scenario: Invalid Build Mode Rejected\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata contains `build_mode = \"docker\"`\n- **WHEN** Pydantic validation runs\n- **THEN** the validator SHALL raise `ValidationError` indicating build_mode must be `local` or `cloud`\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Metadata Save Location\n\nThe system SHALL persist metadata as YAML in a canonical location.\n\n### Scenario: Save Metadata to Canonical Path\n\n- **GIVEN** metadata is updated during pack\n- **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n- **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using:\n  - `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`\n  - `indent=2`\n  - `sort_keys=False`\n  - `model_dump(exclude_none=True)` to exclude None fields\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Pack Result Structure\n\nThe system SHALL return a structured result from `PackRuntime.pack`.\n\n### Scenario: Return Pack Result Dictionary\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime.pack` completes successfully\n- **WHEN** the method returns\n- **THEN** the result SHALL be a `Dict[str, Any]` containing:\n  - `agent_name`: the resolved agent name\n  - `workspace_path`: absolute path to the workspace\n  - `metadata_path`: path to the saved metadata file\n  - `dockerfile_path`: path to generated or existing Dockerfile (or `None`)\n  - `language`: the resolved language\n  - `entrypoint`: the resolved entrypoint command\n  - `port`: the resolved port number\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Global Verbose Logging on Pack\n\nThe system SHALL enable verbose logging when `--verbose` is passed to the pack command.\n\n### Scenario: Verbose Logging Enabled\n\n- **GIVEN** the user passes `--verbose` to the pack command\n- **WHEN** the pack command runs\n- **THEN** `PackRuntime` SHALL:\n  - Set `verbose=True` in the runtime constructor\n  - Log detailed progress messages during each step\n  - Include file paths and intermediate results in logs\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: PackRuntime Initialization\n\nThe system SHALL construct `PackRuntime` with appropriate configuration.\n\n### Scenario: PackRuntime Constructor\n\n- **GIVEN** `PackRuntime(verbose=False)` is constructed\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** the runtime SHALL:\n  - Initialize `MetadataService` for metadata operations\n  - Initialize `DockerService` if Docker integration is needed\n  - Store the `verbose` flag for logging control\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: MetadataOptions Conversion\n\nThe system SHALL convert CLI options to `MetadataOptions` dataclass.\n\n### Scenario: Convert Options to MetadataOptions\n\n- **GIVEN** CLI options dict with keys matching `MetadataOptions` fields\n- **WHEN** `MetadataOptions.from_options(options)` runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL create a `MetadataOptions` instance with:\n  - All optional fields populated from corresponding option values\n  - Defaults applied for missing optional fields per dataclass definition\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Pack Command Error Display\n\nThe system SHALL display errors appropriately based on verbose mode.\n\n### Scenario: Display Error with Traceback in Verbose Mode\n\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs during pack and `verbose=True`\n- **WHEN** `_handle_error` is called\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print `Error packaging agent: {exception_message}` in red via Rich\n  - Print the full Python traceback\n  - Call `typer.Exit(1)` to terminate\n\n### Scenario: Display Error Without Traceback in Non-Verbose Mode\n\n- **GIVEN** an exception occurs during pack and `verbose=False`\n- **WHEN** `_handle_error` is called\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL:\n  - Print `Error packaging agent: {exception_message}` in red via Rich\n  - NOT print traceback\n  - Call `typer.Exit(1)` to terminate\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Workspace Path Resolution\n\nThe system SHALL resolve the workspace path to an absolute path.\n\n### Scenario: Resolve Relative Workspace Path\n\n- **GIVEN** `workspace = \".\"` (relative path)\n- **WHEN** the pack command processes the workspace\n- **THEN** the system SHALL resolve it to an absolute path using `Path(workspace).resolve()`\n\n### Scenario: Resolve Absolute Workspace Path\n\n- **GIVEN** `workspace = \"/home/user/my-agent\"` (absolute path)\n- **WHEN** the pack command processes the workspace\n- **THEN** the system SHALL use the path as-is or normalize it\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Progress Indicator During Pack\n\nThe system SHALL display a progress spinner during pack operations.\n\n### Scenario: Rich Progress Spinner Display\n\n- **GIVEN** the pack command is executing\n- **WHEN** operations like metadata loading, validation, and Dockerfile generation run\n- **THEN** the CLI SHALL display a Rich Progress spinner with descriptive text (e.g., \"Packaging agent...\")\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Multi-File Workspace Handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle workspaces with multiple source files appropriately.\n\n### Scenario: Python Workspace with Multiple Files\n\n- **GIVEN** a Python workspace with `main.py`, `utils.py`, `config.py`, and `requirements.txt`\n- **WHEN** pack runs\n- **THEN** the system SHALL:\n  - Identify all `.py` files for validation\n  - Copy all source files to the packaging context\n  - Include `requirements.txt` in dependency processing\n\n---\n\n## Requirement: Pack Command Help Text\n\nThe system SHALL provide help text for all pack command options.\n\n### Scenario: Pack Command Help Display\n\n- **GIVEN** the user runs `pack --help`\n- **WHEN** the help is displayed\n- **THEN** Typer SHALL show:\n  - Command description\n  - All options with their names, types, defaults, and help strings\n  - Usage examples if configured\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Typer `pack` command definition |\n| `agentcube/runtime/pack_runtime.py` | `PackRuntime` implementation |\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` for metadata operations |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `typer[all]>=0.9.0` | CLI framework with Rich integration |\n| `pydantic>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n| `pyyaml>=6.0` | YAML metadata file handling |\n| `rich>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and error display |\n| `pathlib` | Path resolution and validation |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Pack command registered in Typer app with correct options\n- [ ] Options have correct types and defaults matching spec\n- [ ] Workspace validation checks existence and directory type\n- [ ] Language-specific file validation for Python and Java\n- [ ] Metadata loaded from `agent_metadata.yaml` with fallbacks\n- [ ] New metadata created with defaults when file missing\n- [ ] CLI option overrides applied to metadata\n- [ ] Entrypoint inferred based on language and files\n- [ ] Dockerfile generated with language-specific template\n- [ ] Existing Dockerfile not overwritten\n- [ ] Metadata saved to canonical path with correct YAML format\n- [ ] Pack result returns structured dictionary\n- [ ] Verbose mode enables detailed logging\n- [ ] Error handling prints traceback in verbose mode\n- [ ] Rich Progress spinner displayed during execution\n- [ ] Pydantic validation rejects invalid language/port/build_mode"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775868550770,"end":1775868550910}}}}
